To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Kuwait, you can consider the following transportation options:

1. Walking: Since it is only 1km away, walking could be a convenient and healthy option. Make sure to wear comfortable shoes and stay hydrated, especially during warmer months.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a quicker way to reach the grocery store. Kuwait has dedicated bike lanes in some areas, so check if there are any available near your location.

3. Public Transportation: Kuwait has a reliable bus network. You can check the local bus routes and schedules to see if there is a bus stop close to your location and if it serves the grocery store you want to visit.

4. Taxi or Ride-Share: Taking a taxi or using ride-sharing services like Uber or Careem can be a convenient option, especially if you have heavy groceries to carry or prefer a more comfortable journey. 

Remember to plan your trip in advance, considering factors like weather, traffic conditions, and the accessibility of each transportation option.
